Update to Internet Message Format to
Allow Group Syntax in the From: and
Sender: Header Fields
2013", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="The Internet Message Format (RFC 5322) allows group syntax in some email header fields, such as To: and CC:, but not in From: or Sender:.  This document updates RFC 5322 to relax that restriction, allowing group syntax in those latter fields, as well as in Resent-From: and Resent-Sender:, in certain situations.", style=filled, fillcolor=green]; 

